From: SPR Networks <support@supernetworks.org>
Date: Thu, 22 July 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] add securely authorized SPR krun runtime support

Add private TAP networking, bidirectional Unix/vsock proxying, reliable
external DHCP, OCI guest-rlimit forwarding, and the SPR manager-issued
policy boundary. Privileged host paths and network identities are loaded
only from root-owned policy files; raw krun.* annotations are ignored.

Open trusted paths one component at a time with directory file descriptors
and O_NOFOLLOW, assign sockets per plugin, reject existing listener paths,
validate DHCP replies, and narrow TAP-reclaim races.

Set up TAP networking from the privileged runtime process for both direct
run and split create/start lifecycles.  A fresh start process reloads the
root-owned policy instead of relying on create-child handler state.

